# Validation Loops

## Standard Loop

```
Understand → Plan → Implement → Validate → Analyze → Repair → Revalidate → Review → Complete
```

Integrated into `07-workflow-invocation.mdc` — runs on every task automatically.

## Mandatory Rule

**Never stop after generation. Always validate.**

## Task-Specific Loops

| Task | Loop |
|------|------|
| Feature | Implement → Build → Test → Fix → Retest |
| Bug | Reproduce → Root Cause → Fix → Verify → Regression check |
| Refactor | Refactor → Build → tsc → Behavior compare |
| Docs | Update → Verify facts against code |

## Repository Validation Commands

| Check | Command | When |
|-------|---------|------|
| Production build | `npm run build` | **Always** after code changes |
| TypeScript | `npx tsc --noEmit` | After TS/TSX changes |
| Dev smoke | `npm run dev` | UI/runtime verification |
| Section contract | Verify `id` ↔ nav `#hash` | Section/nav changes |
| Tests | Test runner | When test tooling exists |

## Analyze Phase

On failure:
1. Capture exact error output
2. Classify: implementation, environment, or test issue
3. One focused fix per cycle
4. Re-run full validation after fix

## Repair Limit

**Maximum: 10 iterations.** Then report `INCOMPLETE` with accumulated evidence and blockers.

## Exit Criteria

All `99-completion-gate.mdc` criteria satisfied with evidence. Orchestrator verifies before approval.
